{"priority": "minor", "kind": "bug", "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "links": {"attachments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/246/attachments_page=1.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/246.json"}, "watch": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/246/watch"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/246/comments_page=1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/246/time-limit-for-finals"}, "vote": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/246/vote"}}, "reporter": {"display_name": "Vinayak Jagtap", "uuid": "{4ca9a5d1-e34c-4476-9994-ccb04b8c4c73}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B4ca9a5d1-e34c-4476-9994-ccb04b8c4c73%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B4ca9a5d1-e34c-4476-9994-ccb04b8c4c73%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/d6b7a3e100816973cdc8ca51912fc868d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsVJ-4.png"}}, "nickname": "vinayak_jagtap", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:e3f455ed-c5fc-439b-b24b-e6740163bb87"}, "title": "Time limit for finals", "component": null, "votes": 1, "watches": 3, "content": {"raw": "1. If we start multiple constellations, let's say 2, and run those in parallel. Will that be counted as double the time in the allowed 24 hours or is it counted as the actual time we used for those 2 constellations together?\r\n\r\n2. When we reset due to controller failure (#134, #161, #162, #164, #186, #206),  how much time would we get back for resetting? Can it be the time we used from previous checkpoint completion to the failure point? I understand that the final deadline cannot be extended.\r\n\r\nThis information will help us plan our final runs better. Thanks.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<ol>\n<li>\n<p>If we start multiple constellations, let's say 2, and run those in parallel. Will that be counted as double the time in the allowed 24 hours or is it counted as the actual time we used for those 2 constellations together?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>When we reset due to controller failure (<a href=\"#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/134/javaioioexception-too-many-open-files\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"java.io.IOException: Too many open files\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#134</s></a>, <a href=\"#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/161/stability-issues\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Stability issues\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">#161</a>, <a href=\"#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/162/segfault-in-gazebo-when-robot-moves-out-of\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Segfault in gazebo when robot moves out of start box\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">#162</a>, <a href=\"#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/164/walking-controller-stability-decreases-as\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Walking controller stability decreases as real time factor decreases\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">#164</a>, <a href=\"#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/186/foot-glitches-near-table-on-sample-task-2\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Foot glitches near table on sample task 2\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">#186</a>, <a href=\"#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/206/gazebo-real-time-factor-falls-to-00-in\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Gazebo real time factor falls to 0.0 in srcsim 0.6\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">#206</a>),  how much time would we get back for resetting? Can it be the time we used from previous checkpoint completion to the failure point? I understand that the final deadline cannot be extended.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>This information will help us plan our final runs better. Thanks.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "resolved", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2017-06-11T23:44:00.294031+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2017-06-13T15:28:38.039539+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 246}